Popular comedian Mr Macaroni has revealed he’s at his wit’s end over recent happenings in the country. The skit maker lamented in reaction to a burial video that surfaced which he re-tweeted via his Twitter handle. According to reports from the gruesome video, armed men suspected to be members of a secret cult on Saturday invaded a burial ceremony in Ebenebe, Awka North LGA of Anambra State, killing about 20 persons and leaving several others wounded. They also desecrated the corpse that was being prepared for burial.   Pretty Mike attends party with ladies dressed as animals     I’m honored to be of Kuti clan, says Made     Faithia Williams stages star-studded birthday   Venting his pain, Mr Macaroni explained such happenings as seen in the video discourage him and cause him to wonder where lies humanity among the perpetrators. He tweeted: “Sometimes I really just want to give up! I swear! I see things like this and everything go just tire me because what is this for goodness sake!! “I will continue to do my part in building our nation; hoping that one day Nigeria gets better for you and I. “But for now, I am tired.. I see a lot of things and I am discouraged by our lack of humanity. I’m suffering too much and I don’t know how much more I can take.”